Sentencas: The development of novel oxygen reduction electrodes with superior electrocatalytic activity and CO2 durability is a major challenge for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Insights in to the Electrochemical Activity of Fe-Based Perovskite Cathodes toward Oxygen Reduction Reaction for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Here, novel cobalt-free perovskite oxides, BaFe1-xYxO3-delta (x = 0.05, 0.10, and 0.15) denoted as BFY05, BFY10, and BFY15, are intensively evaluated as oxygen reduction electrode candidate for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Insights in to the Electrochemical Activity of Fe-Based Perovskite Cathodes toward Oxygen Reduction Reaction for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These materials have been synthesized and the electrocatalytic activity for oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) has been investigated systematically.
Titulo: Insights in to the Electrochemical Activity of Fe-Based Perovskite Cathodes toward Oxygen Reduction Reaction for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The BFY10 cathode exhibits the best electrocatalytic performance with a lowest polarization resistance of 0.057 omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C. Meanwhile, the single cells with the BFY05, BFY10 and BFY15 cathodes deliver the peak power densities of 0.73, 1.1, and 0.89 W cm(-2) at 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Insights in to the Electrochemical Activity of Fe-Based Perovskite Cathodes toward Oxygen Reduction Reaction for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, electrochemical impedance spectra (EIS) are analyzed by means of distribution of relaxation time (DRT).
Titulo: Insights in to the Electrochemical Activity of Fe-Based Perovskite Cathodes toward Oxygen Reduction Reaction for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The results indicate that the oxygen adsorption-dissociation process is determined to be the rate-limiting step at the electrode interface.
Titulo: Insights in to the Electrochemical Activity of Fe-Based Perovskite Cathodes toward Oxygen Reduction Reaction for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In addition, the single cell with the BFY10 cathode exhibits a good long-term stability at 700 degrees C under an output voltage of 0.5 V for 120 h.
Titulo: Insights in to the Electrochemical Activity of Fe-Based Perovskite Cathodes toward Oxygen Reduction Reaction for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
